name: shawnHarris()
tweet: Facilitated Network - Structured to enable the exchange of products and services - Customers pay fees to the network, which in turn pays the service provider  Examples: OpenIDEO, CEB, Gerson Lehrman Group, Eden McCallum, BTG

name: shawnHarris()
tweet: Value-Added Process Business - Structured to address problems of defined scope with standard processes - Processes are usually repeatable and controllable - Customers pay for output only  Examples: Motista,  http://Salesforce.com , McKinsey Solutions

name: shawnHarris()
tweet: Solution Shop - Structured to diagnose and solve problems whose scope is undefined - Delivers value primarily through consultants’ judgment rather than through repeatable processes - Customers pay high prices in the form of fee-for-service  Examples: McKinsey, Bain, BCG, IDEO

name: shawnHarris()
tweet: Consulting: Three Business Models - Solution Shop - Value-Added Process Business - Facilitated Network  #leadership #strategy #Solutions
